@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<p>
    "Coinpanion" is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your personal information.
</p>

<h2>1. Data Collection:</h2>
<p>
    "Coinpanion" collects and stores user-provided data, including but not limited to expense details (date, amount, category).
</p>

<h2>2. Data Usage:</h2>
<p>
    The collected data is used solely for the purpose of managing and tracking user expenses within the "Coinpanion" application.
</p>

<h2>3. Data Security:</h2>
<p>
    We prioritize the security of your data and implement industry-standard measures to protect it from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction.
</p>

<h2>4. Data Access:</h2>
<p>
    Access to your expense data is restricted to authenticated users. We do not share, sell, or provide access to your data to third parties.
</p>

<h2>5. Cookies:</h2>
<p>
    "Coinpanion" uses cookies to enhance user experience. These cookies are used for authentication and do not track personal browsing habits.
</p>

<h2>6. Third-Party Integration:</h2>
<p>
    Any third-party integrations (if applicable) adhere to strict privacy standards. We do not share your data with third-party services without your explicit consent.
</p>

<h2>7. Data Retention:</h2>
<p>
    Your expense data is retained for as long as your account is active. You can request data deletion at any time, and we will promptly comply.
</p>

<h2>8. Communication:</h2>
<p>
    "Coinpanion" may occasionally send important updates or notifications related to your account and the application.
</p>

<h2>9. Compliance:</h2>
<p>
    We comply with relevant data protection laws and regulations to ensure your privacy is respected and protected.
</p>

<h2>10. User Control:</h2>
<p>
    You have control over your data. You can review, edit, or delete your expense records within the application.
</p>
